This paper deals with the restricted isometry property (RIP) of low rank matrices, which is a topic closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on subspace projection matrices also suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the study of stable embedding of submanifolds could be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) or scientific computing (cs.SI).
